24/10/2002
VIENNA, Austria -- President Thomas Klestil on Wednesday (23 October) reaffirmed support for Romania's accession into the EU, during a meeting with Romanian counterpart Ion Iliescu. For his part, Iliescu called for a higher level of economic co-operation, matching that of political relations between the two governments. He also called on Austrian banks and companies to participate in Romania's privatisation process. (Rompres, Mediafax - 23/10/02, Nine o'Clock - 24/10/02)
